Heptathela goulouensis
Yin, 2001: 297 (♀♀, from Gouloufeng, Hengyang City, Hunan Province, China, collected by X.J. Peng on 1 August 1997; deposited in HNU, examined); 
Yin 2001
: 2; Yin et al. 2012: 114;

Palp
.

Paracymbium unpigmented and unsclerotized in prolateral view, with numerous setae and spines on the tip (Fig. 
7A
); contrategulum with serrate margin (Fig. 
7A, D, G
); tegulum with a dentate marginal apophysis and the dorsal extension of terminal apophysis, and with a small terminal apophysis in retrolateral view (Fig. 
7C, F
); the smooth conductor base fused with embolus, with two free apical spines, the short one located at the one third of the conductor and close to the conductor margin, the long one extended over the embolus opening (Fig. 
7A, B, D, E
); embolus distal margin slightly curved, with a wide and flat opening (Fig. 
7A-F
).
